31/01/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The National Integrity Agency announced on Friday (January 29th) that it is investigating Senate Speaker Mircea Geoana for filing a questionable declaration of assets. 
The agency said that the case has been handed over to the chief prosecutor for further investigation. 
Geoana, of the Social Democratic Party, ran for president late last year but lost to incumbent Traian Basescu. 
(Adevarul, Realitatea, Evenimentul Zilei, AFP - 29/01/10)
